FBIS4-48759 "drafr102_c_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-102 Daily Report 26 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Mandela Meets With Democratic Party's Leon Mandela Meets With Democratic Party's Leon MB2605095594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0739 GMT 26 May 94 MB2605095594 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Cape Town May 26 SAPA -- President Nelson Mandela held discussions over breakfast with acting Democratic Party [DP] leader Mr Tony Leon at Mr Mandela's official residence Westbrooke on Thursday. Mr Mandela's spokesman, Mr Joel Netshitenzhe, described the meeting a "courtesy call". Mr Leon said they discussed the DP's role as an opposition party and its future relationship with the government. He said the talks were "friendly". Mr Netshitenzhe said Mr Mandela would also be meeting with Pan Africanist Congress leader, Mr Clarence Makwetu, some time on Thursday.
